  exerciseName: Factorial
  exerciseTitle: Factorial
  exerciseText: 'Write a function that calculates the Factorial of a given number.

    The
    Factorial is the product of all positive integers.

    For example the factorial
    of 3 is: 3 * 2 * 1;

    The factorial of n is: n * (n - 1) * (n - 2) * ... *
    1;

'
  hintText: 'The math is: n * (n - 1) * (n - 2) * ... * 1;

    So think of what
    your function needs to return, it needs to return a number * calling itself,
    and eventually needs to return 1;'
  solutionText: "public int CalculateFactorial(int n) {\r\n    if (n == 1) {\r\n       
    return 1;\r\n    } else {\r\n        return n * CalculateFactorial(n - 1);\r\n   
    }\r\n}"
  completedText: Here you learned how to implement a Factorial using recursion.
